@ContentNegotiationDemo_HostAddress = https://localhost:7299

### 1. Basics - No Accept header
GET {{ContentNegotiationDemo_HostAddress}}/api/basics/employee

###

### 2. Basics - JSON response
GET {{ContentNegotiationDemo_HostAddress}}/api/basics/employee
Accept: application/json

###

### 3. Basics - XML response
GET {{ContentNegotiationDemo_HostAddress}}/api/basics/employee
Accept: application/xml

###

### 4. Format selection - Multiple Accept values, XML first
GET {{ContentNegotiationDemo_HostAddress}}/api/format-selection/employee/1
Accept: application/xml,application/json

###

### 5. Format selection - Multiple Accept values, JSON first
GET {{ContentNegotiationDemo_HostAddress}}/api/format-selection/employee/1
Accept: application/json,application/xml

###

### 6. Input negotiation - Create employee with JSON body and ask JSON response
POST {{ContentNegotiationDemo_HostAddress}}/api/input-negotiation/employees
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "Name": "Meena",
  "Department": "Support",
  "Salary": 45000,
  "Email": "meena@demo.com"
}

###

### 7. Input negotiation - Create employee with JSON body and ask XML response
POST {{ContentNegotiationDemo_HostAddress}}/api/input-negotiation/employees
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/xml

{
  "Name": "Suresh",
  "Department": "Operations",
  "Salary": 51000,
  "Email": "suresh@demo.com"
}

###

### 8. Strict negotiation - Unsupported Accept header should return 406
GET {{ContentNegotiationDemo_HostAddress}}/api/strict-negotiation/employee
Accept: text/csv

###

### 9. Strict negotiation - Supported JSON request
GET {{ContentNegotiationDemo_HostAddress}}/api/strict-negotiation/employee
Accept: application/json
